sheds new light on how the Daoist classic, which has often been seen as a timeless book of wisdom, is situated in its historical context, while also considering it as a guide to personal cultivation and self-realization.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2022) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Asian / Chinese.2bisacsh1 aLynn, Richard John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311074966340uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/lynn1238640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231556453423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780231556453/original  a978-3-11-074966-3  Columbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles